  <BR>
<p><a href="/cf-bin/attendee/Confplanneraction.cfm?CID=728"><img src="/Graphics/cf-bin/planner/Add2Planner.gif" width=110 height=34 border=0 align="right" alt="Add to planner"></a>All the new entertainment technologies entering the home will have short-lived success without a clear                         vision and direction provided by entertainment content providers. The film, television and music industries                         are now all in the midst of a tremendous experiment in trial and error. With so many platforms to produce                         for, from an expanding cable TV universe, new game and home video formats, to the Internet and its                         broadband possibilities and the coming of DTV, the coming years will be an era of never-ending expansion.                         In this session our speakers come from companies committed to bringing about that change. Entertainment                         convergence is not theory to them, it is everyday practice. <P><BR> 

Thursday, January 6&nbsp; from &nbsp;04:00 PM - 
05:15 PM<BR><br>
  <b>Room:</b>&nbsp; LVCC N260</font><p>
